        String name = startTag.normalName();

        if (StringUtil.in(name, "th", "td")) {
            // Close any open cell before inserting a new one
            if (tb.inTableScope("th") || tb.inTableScope("td")) {
                tb.processEndTag("th"); // or "td", but close whatever is open
            }
            tb.clearStackToTableRowContext();
            tb.insert(startTag);
            tb.transition(InCell);
            tb.insertMarkerToFormattingElements();
        } else if (StringUtil.in(name, "caption", "col", "colgroup", "tbody", "tfoot", "thead", "tr")) {
            return handleMissingTr(t, tb);
        } else {
            return anythingElse(t, tb);
        }
    } else if (t.isEndTag()) {
        Token.EndTag endTag = t.asEndTag();
        String name = endTag.normalName();

        if (name.equals("tr")) {
            if (!tb.inTableScope(name)) {
                tb.error(this); // frag
                return false;
            }
            // Close any open cells before closing the row
            while (tb.currentElement().normalName().equals("th") || tb.currentElement().normalName().equals("td")) {
                tb.processEndTag(tb.currentElement().normalName());
            }
            tb.clearStackToTableRowContext();
            tb.pop(); // tr
            tb.transition(InTableBody);
        } else if (name.equals("table")) {
            return handleMissingTr(t, tb);
        } else if (StringUtil.in(name, "tbody", "tfoot", "thead")) {
            if (!tb.inTableScope(name)) {
                tb.error(this);
                return false;
            }
            tb.processEndTag("tr");
            return tb.process(t);
        } else if (StringUtil.in(name, "body", "caption", "col", "colgroup", "html", "td", "th")) {
            tb.error(this);
            return false;
        } else {
            return anythingElse(t, tb);
        }
    } else {
        return anythingElse(t, tb);
    }
    return true;
}
```

This fix adds loops to close open cells before closing a row or body. This matches the HTML spec requirement of generating implied end tags for cells.

Now, which testcases would trigger this bug? Any test that has unclosed cells before a row or body end tag. For example, `handlesNestedImplicitTable` has `<tr><td>1</td></tr>` but also inner table, might cause open cells. `ignoresDupeEndTrTag` has a duplicate tr end tag with an open cell? Actually, it has `<tr><td>Two</td></tr></tr>` which leaves a tr open after the first end? Possibly. `noTableDirectInTable` has multiple tables. `handlesImplicitCaptionClose` has caption then td directly.

So these tests are likely to be affected.

